The paper deals with information theoretic analysis of the secrecy capacity of MSR codes under a passive eavesdropping model, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The analysis involves investigating the properties of storage nodes and repair traffic, which can be related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and security and privacy (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the amount of data downloaded from each helper node during the repair process, which can be related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
